MGetz  December 28, 2022


  1  Collapse this comment
Copy link
The original IBM PC only had five, the XT was a later model. You could in fact later buy an entire separate case (XT style case) with another 7 slots of expansion. Why 7 because one was required to bridge to the original IBM PC. This meant you’d have 11 total usable as one in the IBM PC would be taken up for the bridge. The case had its own PSU too.




