Reminds me of my favorite Microsoft product ever, the Z80 Softcard which let you run CP/M on your Apple ][.  I did my AP Computer Science course running CP/M Turbo Pascal running on these, worked great (MUCH better than Apple Pascal which was a virtual machine and slow as molasses).  Surprisingly (to me), Wikipedia says this was actually really popular and Microsoft’s top revenue source for 1980.





